Part I - ProsperLoan Dataset Exploration and Analysis¶

By: Yaji Timothy T.¶

Introduction¶

The data set that i choose for projecct III is the Prosperloan data. Prosper is a P2P lending platform that allows investors to choose among personal loans to invest in. They do that by considering a number of factors, that has to do with borrower social economic attributes and the performance and the risk for each loan, among others.There are many questions one could ask of this data, but in this project I will focus on investigate the determining factors of loan delinquency from the perspective of borrower attributes and loan characteristics.

High loan delinquencies could lead to a liquidity problem that causes financial institution to fall and jeopardizing the country’s economy. The principles of good lending state that a loan should not be granted to a borrower until the source of repayment is reasonably certain. 1.

For ease of analysis i will be select just a few variables that i believe have to do with borrower attributes and loan characteristics.

This number is one way lenders measure your ability to manage the monthly payments to repay the money you plan to borrow. This is our dependent variable, (Variable of intrest). To simplify the problem, and to retain data, let's classify all "past Due","Chargedoff and "Defaulted" as delinquent, reason can be found here and all others (Current", "cancelled","FinalPaymentInProgress", and "completed") as None Delinquent. Let's encode those binary outcomes as 1 and 0, respectively.

In [22]:
# Create variable of interest DelinquentStatus
Non_delinquent=["FinalPaymentInProgress","Cancelled", "Current", "Completed"]
Delinquentloan_list=[]
for row in df_loan_selected.LoanStatus:
        if row in Non_delinquent: Delinquentloan_list. append (0)
        else:Delinquentloan_list.append(1)
# asign the list to values new column
df_loan_selected['DelinquentStatus'] = Delinquentloan_list

Create a new column "CreditScore" based on the classification provided on Esperian

  • First, we have to create empty list and name it CrScore_list
  • write a for loop functions which we will append and assign values as per the conditition below:

CreditScoreRangeUpper is less than or equal to 579 asssign it "Poor"

CreditScoreRangeUpper between 580-669, asign it "Fair"

CreditScoreRangeUpper between 670-739, asign it "Good"

CreditScoreRangeUpper between 740-799, asign it "Very Good"

CreditScoreRangeUpper is from 800 above, asign it "Exceptional"

  • Convert list into column of dataframe
In [26]:
#create an empty list
CrScore_list = []
'''
created a loop which will iterate over all the rows in column 'CreditScoreRangeUpper' and assign 
values to CrScore_list. We are using if-else function to make the conditons specified above
'''
for row in df_loan_selected["CreditScoreRangeUpper"]:
    if row <= 579:
        CrScore_list.append("Poor")
    elif row <=669:
        CrScore_list.append("Fair")
    elif row <=739:
        CrScore_list.append("Good")
    elif row<=799:
        CrScore_list.append("Very Good")
    else:
        CrScore_list.append("Exceptional")
In [27]:
#Converting list into column of dataset and viewing the final dataset
df_loan_selected["CreditScore"]=CrScore_list

# Convert 'ListingCreationDate' type from str to datetime 
df_loan_selected['ListingCreationDate']=pd.to_datetime(df_loan_selected['ListingCreationDate'])

df_loan_selected['Year'] = df_loan_selected['ListingCreationDate'].dt.year

df_loan_selected['Quarter'] = pd.PeriodIndex(df_loan_selected["ListingCreationDate"], freq='Q')

df_loan_selected.sort_values(by=['Quarter'], inplace=True)

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

There are 105462 loans in the dataset with 17 features. The variables are numeric and categorical in nature. And the variables are:

'Year', 'Quarter', 'ListingCategory', 'LoanOriginalAmount', 'Term', 'BorrowerRate', 'MonthlyLoanPayment', 'StatedMonthlyIncome', 'IncomeVerifiable', 'DebtToIncomeRatio', 'CreditScore', 'OpenRevolvingAccounts', 'EmploymentStatus', 'IsBorrowerHomeowner', 'CurrentlyInGroup', 'Occupation', 'BorrowerState', 'DelinquentStatus'

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

I'm interested in the Delinquent loans, most especially looking that: DelinquencyStatus and MonthyLoanPayment.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

There are so many features to explore, I suppose that the following features would have the largest effect on delinquent loans:

  • CreditScore: The Credit rating that was assigned at the time the listing went live.
  • BorrowerRate : The interest rate on the loan
  • Term : Term of loan
  • DebToIncomeRatio - The debt to income ratio of the borrower at the time the credit profile was pulled.
  • IsBorrowerHouseOwner: A Borrower will be classified as a homowner if they have a mortgage on their credit profile or provide documentation confirming they are a homeowner.
  • IncomeVerifiable : Is the

Please note that it is not an exhaustive list of delinquecy loans determinant. Additional features might be required.

Most of my cleaning efforts and adjustment were on ordering factors levels to make more intuitive sense and replaceing missing valuesfor non-numeric variables with Unkown and possibly dropping null values in numeric variables

Conclusions¶

In analysig the loan portfolios, we created DelinquentStatus from LoanStatus. To simplify the problem of selecting delinquent loans, and to retain data, we classify all "past Due", chargedoff", cancellation, and "defaulted" and "CurrentLoan" as delinquent, reason can be found here and all others ( "completed" and "CurrentPaymentInprogress') as None Delinquent. And encode those binary outcomes as 1 and 0, respectively. I also recode CreditScore and changed it to a categorical variable to better interprete the data.

Most of my cleaning efforts where on handling missing values,removing duplicates, and ordering factors levels to make more intuitive sense in visualization.

summary of findings¶

  • Delinquent loans constitute 15.16% of the loans in the portfolio
  • Only 7.62% of borrowers don't have their income verified have thier loans delinquent
  • Borrowers with good credit score have the highest number of delinquent loans.
  • 36 months term loans has the highest number and total amount of delinquent loans with its listing category as not available.
  • Over the years delinquency fluctuates with its peaks in 2009
  • Loan monthly payment correlates with BorrowerAPR and Loan Origination Amount.
  • The correlation coefficient of Monthly loan payment and borrower APR is -0.23, the scatter plot also shows that these two variables are negatively correlated, that is the more the monthly loan payment amount, the lower the APR.

  • The loan original amount is positively correlated with the monthly Loan payment, it makes sense since the more money you borrow the more money you pay monthly.

  • We observe that a positive relationship between credit score, Monthly loan payment and delinquent status.
